<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3336908>
    dc:description "FIGURE 117. A: Bocchus ruvidus Olmi, Copeland & van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype in dorsal view; head vertex and mesoscu- tum sculpture. B–D: habitus of Dryinus species. B–C: ♀ in dorsal (B) and lateral (C) view; D: ♂ in dorsal view. Scale bar: A: 1.86 mm; B: 3.63 mm; C: 2.82 mm; D: 2.67 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3336908/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3336926>
    dc:description "FIGURE 126. Chelae of Dryinus species. A: D. chamaeleo Benoit, holotype. B: D. copelandi Olmi, holotype. C: D. daviesi Olmi, holotype. D: D. dayianus Olmi, holotype. E: D. deceptor (Turner), ♀ from South Africa, Port St. Johns. F: D. digo Olmi, Copeland & Guglielmino, holotype. Scale bar: A: 0.17 mm; B: 0.10 mm; C: 0.11 mm; D: 0.16 mm; E: 0.15 mm; F: 0.22 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3336926/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3336912>
    dc:description "FIGURE 119. A: chela of Dryinus sp. group 4. B–E: Dryinus afer (Olmi): head in dorsal view (B), prothorax in lateral view (C), chela (E) of ♀ holotype; genitalia (D) of ♂ allotype. Scale bar:A: 0.11 mm; B: 0.24 mm; C: 0.49 mm; D: 0.08 mm; E: 0.16 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3336912/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3336910>
    dc:description "FIGURE 118. Habitus of Dryinus species. A: ♂ in lateral view. B, C: D. afer (Olmi), ♀ holotype in dorsal (B) and lateral (C) view. Scale bar: A: 1.60 mm; B: 3.56 mm; C: 2.83 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3336910/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3336664>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. A, B: chelae. C, D: mesosoma of Bocchinae (C) and Dryininae (D) ♂♂ in lateral view. a: arolium; e: enlarged claw; m: mesopleuron; p: pronotum; r: rudimentary claw; s: protarsomere 5; t: tegula; z: epicnemium. E: forewing of fictitious specimen (C: costal cell; cv: costal vein; Pt: pterostigma; R: radial cell; 1Cu: first cubital cell; 2Cu: second cubital cell; 2R1: second radial 1 cell; 2r-rs&Rs: second radial cross & radial sector vein; PostabR1: poststigmal abscissa of Radial1 vein)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3336664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

